        <chapter>  
            <title>&lt;Introduction to> ISAAC</title>
            <!--This chapter will introduce: (2) ISAAC: service / backend [API/algorithm/computation]-->
            <itemizedlist>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Contains a robust Core set of Microservices to facilitate the API </para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Utilizes Lucene searching functionality to provide "smart" computed searches against the SOLOR data store</para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Designed to be extensable for various data store providers and back-ends</para>
                </listitem>
            </itemizedlist>
        </chapter>
        
        <chapter>  
            <title>&lt;Introduction to> SOLOR</title>
            <!--This chapter will introduce: (3) SOLOR : data store / persistance layer [database]"-->
            <xi:include href="../../target/extracted-dependencies/sh.isaac.komet.doc/appendices/requirements-enumeration-kc.xml" xpointer="para_l1n_vrr_dbb"/>
            <xi:include href="../../target/extracted-dependencies/sh.isaac.komet.doc/appendices/requirements-enumeration-kc.xml" xpointer="itemizedlist_q1n_vrr_dbb"/>
            <itemizedlist>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Designed from a custom byte/binary file format and integrated with lucene indexing to provide efficent computated queries</para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Contains a "schema" consisting of Concepts and Attachements which are used in optomized computed pathing queries</para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Each element stored in SOLOR is designed to have loose coupling and contain associated references to other elements</para>
                </listitem>
            </itemizedlist>
        </chapter>
        
